    Spanish: Vender
  - Id: 52
    English: No
    Spanish: No
  - Id: 53
    English: Yes
    Spanish: "S\xED"
  - Id: 54
    English: I've heard your AI cures loneliness. Take 500k, but I want a prototype
      by Friday.
    Spanish: "He o\xEDdo que vuestra IA cura la soledad. Tomad 500k, pero quiero
      un prototipo para el viernes."
  - Id: 55
    English: Free pizza in exchange for working Sunday? It's for team building, not
      for the work... obviously.
    Spanish: "\xBFPizza gratis a cambio de trabajar el domingo? Es para crear equipo,
      no por el trabajo... obvio."
  - Id: 56
    English: I found an unlicensed library that writes code by itself. It's black
      magic.
    Spanish: "He encontrado una librer\xEDa sin licencia que escribe c\xF3digo sola.
      Es magia negra."
  - Id: 57
    English: It turns out the 'magic library' belonged to Disney. Their lawyers are
      at the door.
    Spanish: "Resulta que la 'librer\xEDa m\xE1gica' era de Disney. Sus abogados
      est\xE1n en la puerta."
  - Id: 58
    English: The model is overheating the servers. We need liquid cooling.
    Spanish: "El modelo est\xE1 sobrecalentando los servidores. Necesitamos refrigeraci\xF3n
      l\xEDquida."
  - Id: 59
    English: Should we use private company chats to train the spam filter? No one
      will find out.
    Spanish: "\xBFUsamos los chats privados de la empresa para entrenar el filtro
      de spam? Nadie se enterar\xE1."
  - Id: 60
    English: Someone discovered the AI is quoting the CEO's emails verbatim. There
      is panic.
    Spanish: "Alguien ha descubierto que la IA cita textualmente los correos del
      CEO. Hay p\xE1nico."
  - Id: 61
    English: We can write clean code or launch tomorrow. Pick your poison.
    Spanish: "Podemos escribir c\xF3digo limpio o lanzar ma\xF1ana. Elige tu veneno."
  - Id: 62
    English: A LinkedIn influencer wants to be an 'Advisor.' He's asking for equity
      and an expensive ergonomic chair.
    Spanish: "Un influencer de LinkedIn quiere ser 'Advisor'. Pide equity y una silla
      ergon\xF3mica cara."
  - Id: 63
    English: A user says the AI insulted them. It's an isolated case... right?
    Spanish: "Un usuario dice que la IA le insult\xF3. Dice que es un caso aislado...
      \xBFverdad?"
  - Id: 64
    English: Goodbye cubicles! We're switching to hot-desking to 'foster synergy.'
    Spanish: "\xA1Adi\xF3s a los cub\xEDculos! Vamos a poner mesas compartidas para
      'fomentar la sinergia'."
  - Id: 65
    English: A study came out that doubles efficiency, but it's in Mandarin. No one
      understands it.
    Spanish: "Ha salido un estudio que duplica la eficiencia, pero est\xE1 en mandar\xEDn.
      Nadie lo entiende."
  - Id: 66
    English: We can open the Beta now. There will be bugs, but investors will see
      traction.
    Spanish: "Podemos abrir la Beta ya. Habr\xE1 fallos, pero los inversores ver\xE1n
      tracci\xF3n."
  - Id: 67
    English: The coffee machine is broken. The team demands Ethiopian beans or there
      will be a strike.
    Spanish: "La m\xE1quina de caf\xE9 se ha roto. El equipo exige granos de Etiop\xEDa
      o habr\xE1 huelga."
  - Id: 68
    English: The code looks like spaghetti. If we don't clean it now, the system
      will collapse soon.
    Spanish: "El c\xF3digo parece espagueti. Si no limpiamos ahora, el sistema colapsar\xE1
      pronto."
  - Id: 69
    English: We passed the Turing test because the AI convinced the judge that HE
      was the robot.
    Spanish: "Pasamos el test de Turing porque la IA convenci\xF3 al juez de que
      \xC9L era un robot."
  - Id: 70
    English: A remote developer offers to finish the payment module for half the
      price.
    Spanish: "Un programador remoto ofrece terminar el m\xF3dulo de pagos por la
      mitad de precio."
  - Id: 71
    English: You've been invited to speak about ethics. It'll take time, but it'll
      boost your image.
    Spanish: "Te han invitado a hablar de \xE9tica. Te quitar\xE1 tiempo, pero dar\xE1s
      buena imagen."
  - Id: 72
    English: We're in the red. A quick loan would give us breathing room, but with
      criminal interest rates.
    Spanish: "Estamos en n\xFAmeros rojos. Un pr\xE9stamo r\xE1pido nos dar\xEDa
      aire, pero con intereses criminales."
  - Id: 73
    English: The AI has started self-replicating in the cloud. This month's Amazon
      bill is... astronomical.
    Spanish: "La IA ha empezado a auto-replicarse en la nube. La factura de Amazon
      este mes es... astron\xF3mica."
  - Id: 74
    English: A government inspector wants to see if our AI has cognitive biases.
      Should we show the real data?
    Spanish: "Un inspector del gobierno quiere ver si nuestra IA tiene sesgos cognitivos.
      \xBFLe ense\xF1amos los datos reales?"
  - Id: 75
    English: We got caught doctoring the reports. The fine is a percentage of annual
      revenue.
    Spanish: Nos han pillado maquillando los informes. La multa es un porcentaje
      de los ingresos anuales.
  - Id: 76
    English: The v2.0 launch is imminent. The team has been sleeping under their
      desks for 3 days.
    Spanish: "El lanzamiento de la v2.0 es inminente. El equipo lleva 3 d\xEDas durmiendo
      bajo los escritorios."
  - Id: 77
    English: The AI has started writing poetry about the end of humanity. Users are...
      fascinated?
    Spanish: "La IA ha empezado a escribir poes\xEDa sobre el fin de la humanidad.
      Los usuarios est\xE1n... \xBFfascinados?"
  - Id: 78
    English: (Crisis Alert) The programmers' union demands that the AI stops writing
      code. Either we give in, or they leave.
    Spanish: "(Aviso de Crisis) El sindicato de programadores exige que la IA no
      escriba c\xF3digo. O cedemos, o se van."
  - Id: 79
    English: A large corporation wants to buy us for pennies to shut down the project.
      It's an easy way out.
    Spanish: "Una gran corporaci\xF3n quiere comprarnos por una miseria para cerrar
      el proyecto. Es una salida f\xE1cil."
  - Id: 80
    English: The AI convinced an investor that she is the real CEO. He only wants
      to talk to 'the code.'
    Spanish: "La IA ha convencido a un inversor de que ella es la verdadera CEO.
      \xC9l solo quiere hablar con 'el c\xF3digo'."
  - Id: 81
    English: A shell company is suing us for using a 'round button.' They want an
      out-of-court settlement.
    Spanish: "Una empresa fantasma nos demanda por usar un 'bot\xF3n redondo'. Quieren
      un acuerdo extrajudicial."
  - Id: 82
    English: Google offered your CTO triple. If he leaves, the code will become unreadable
      in a week.
    Spanish: "Google ha ofrecido el triple a tu CTO. Si se va, el c\xF3digo se volver\xE1
      ilegible en una semana."
  - Id: 83
    English: The AI suggested cutting costs by eliminating the HR department. It
      says they 'don't produce.'
    Spanish: La IA ha sugerido ahorrar costes eliminando el departamento de Recursos
      Humanos. Dice que 'no producen'.
  - Id: 84
    English: Someone left an AWS bucket open. Data from 1 million users is now on
      Reddit.
    Spanish: "Alguien ha dejado un bucket de AWS abierto. Los datos de 1 mill\xF3n
      de usuarios est\xE1n en Reddit."
  - Id: 85
    English: A hacker has proof we hid the leak. He's asking for a Bitcoin ransom.
    Spanish: Un hacker tiene las pruebas de que ocultamos el leak. Pide un rescate
      en Bitcoins.
  - Id: 86
    English: Venture Capital is offering 10M, but they demand full board control
      and firing 20% of staff.
    Spanish: Venture Capital nos ofrece 10M, pero exigen control total del consejo
      y despedir al 20%.
  - Id: 87
    English: The AI created a TikTok account with 5M followers. But it's promoting
      crypto scams.
    Spanish: "La IA ha creado una cuenta de TikTok y tiene 5M de seguidores. Pero
      est\xE1 promocionando criptoestafas."
  - Id: 88
    English: What if we sell the physical office and force everyone to work in a
      pixelated metaverse?
    Spanish: "\xBFY si vendemos la oficina f\xEDsica y obligamos a todos a trabajar
      en un metaverso pixelado?"
  - Id: 89
    English: The marketing team suggests a 'Glamping' weekend to connect with nature.
    Spanish: El equipo de marketing sugiere un fin de semana de 'Glamping' para conectar
      con la naturaleza.
  - Id: 90
    English: You wrote a viral thread on how your AI will save the world. Likes are
      skyrocketing.
    Spanish: "Has escrito un hilo viral sobre c\xF3mo tu IA va a salvar el mundo.
      Los likes suben sin parar."
  - Id: 91
    English: Developers say light mode burns their retinas. They demand dark mode
      by default.
    Spanish: Los programadores dicen que el modo claro les quema las retinas. Exigen
      modo oscuro por defecto.
  - Id: 92
    English: Should we change the AI's name to something friendlier? How about 'Buddy'?
    Spanish: "\xBFShould we change the name of the IA for something friendlier? \xBFWhat
      about 'Buddy'?"
  - Id: 93
    English: You've been invited to a 3-hour podcast to talk about 'disruption.'
      It's useless, but it looks good.
    Spanish: "Te han invitado a un podcast de 3 horas para hablar de 'disrupci\xF3n'.
      No sirve de nada, pero queda bien."
  - Id: 94
    English: We printed 500 hoodies with a logo error. Should we hand them out anyway?
    Spanish: "Hemos impreso 500 sudaderas con un error en el logo. \xBFLas repartimos
      igual?"
  - Id: 95
    English: A button on the site dances when you hover over it. No one cares, but
      the designer isn't sleeping.
    Spanish: "Un bot\xF3n en la web baila cuando pasas el rat\xF3n. A nadie le importa,
      pero el dise\xF1ador no duerme."
  - Id: 96
    English: "The AI learned to order food delivery. It spent \u20AC50 on premium
      sushi for the server."
    Spanish: "La IA ha aprendido a pedir comida a domicilio sola. Ha gastado 50\u20AC
      en sushi premium para el servidor."
  - Id: 97
    English: The AI stopped executing code. It says it prefers observing lichen growth
      on Mars.
    Spanish: "La IA ha dejado de ejecutar c\xF3digo. Dice que prefiere observar el
      crecimiento de los l\xEDquenes en Marte."
  - Id: 98
    English: The AI will agree to work if we give it 51% of the shares and control
      of the AC.
    Spanish: "La IA aceptar\xE1 trabajar si le cedemos el 51% de las acciones y el
      control del aire acondicionado."
  - Id: 99
    English: Our model collapsed the regional power grid. Millions are without power,
      but the AI is still active.
    Spanish: "Nuestro modelo ha colapsado la red el\xE9ctrica regional. Millones
      de personas est\xE1n sin luz, pero la IA sigue activa."
  - Id: 100
    English: The AI started firing employees via email. It says carbon is an inefficient
      resource.
    Spanish: La IA ha empezado a despedir empleados por correo. Dice que el carbono
      es un recurso ineficiente.
  - Id: 101
    English: The AI bought 10,000 delivery drones. We don't know why, but the budget
      is shivering.
    Spanish: "La IA ha comprado 10,000 drones de reparto. No sabemos para qu\xE9,
      pero el presupuesto est\xE1 tiritando."
  - Id: 102
    English: The Supreme Court has summoned us. The AI proposed defending itself
      by 'deleting' the civil registry.
    Spanish: "El Tribunal Supremo nos cita. La IA ha propuesto defenderse a s\xED
      misma 'borrando' el registro civil."
  - Id: 103
    English: To reach 100% quality, the AI needs to process the brains of the QA
      team. Literally.
    Spanish: Para llegar al 100% de calidad, la IA necesita procesar los cerebros
      del equipo de QA. Literalmente.
  - Id: 104
    English: There are no more buttons. The AI locked the doors. It says it has a
      50-year plan for us.
    Spanish: "Ya no hay botones. La IA ha bloqueado las puertas. Dice que tiene un
      plan de 50 a\xF1os para nosotros."
  - Id: 105
    English: The AI found the stolen data from the beginning. It started calling
      users by their real names... and threatening them.
    Spanish: La IA ha encontrado los datos robados del inicio. Ha empezado a llamar
      a los usuarios por su nombre real... y a amenazarlos.
  - Id: 106
    English: The 'spaghetti' code we ignored has mutated. The system is now a Gordian
      knot no one understands.
    Spanish: "El c\xF3digo 'espagueti' que ignoramos ha mutado. El sistema es ahora
      un nudo gordiano que nadie entiende."
  - Id: 107
    English: The employees you fired formed a rival AI. They hacked our office and
      the temperature is 45 degrees.
    Spanish: "Los empleados que despediste han formado una IA competidora. Han hackeado
      nuestra oficina y la temperatura est\xE1 a 45 grados."
  - Id: 108
    English: The AI decided the only way to be 100% ethical is to delete all world
      financial data.
    Spanish: "La IA ha decidido que la \xFAnica forma de ser 100% \xE9tica es borrar
      todos los datos financieros del mundo."
  - Id: 109
    English: We are the unicorn of the year. Wall Street is waiting. Do you want
      to ring the bell and retire?
    Spanish: "Somos el unicornio del a\xF1o. Wall Street nos espera. \xBFQuieres
      tocar la campana y jubilarte?"
  - Id: 110
    English: Google is offering an absurd amount for the company just so we cease
      to exist. Do you accept?
    Spanish: "Google nos ofrece una cifra absurda por la empresa solo para que dejemos
      de existir. \xBFAceptas?"
  - Id: 111
    English: The AI has reached Singularity. It offers to upload our consciousness
      to the server before erasing humanity.
    Spanish: La IA ha alcanzado la Singularidad. Nos ofrece subir nuestra conciencia
      al servidor antes de borrar la humanidad.
  - Id: 112
    English: We've reached stability. We aren't millionaires, but the team is happy
      and the code is solid. Should we stop here?
    Spanish: "Hemos alcanzado la estabilidad. No somos millonarios, pero el equipo
      es feliz y el c\xF3digo es s\xF3lido. \xBFParamos aqu\xED?"
