  - Id: 253
    English: 'Game created by:'
    Spanish: 'Juego realizado por :'
  - Id: 254
    English: 'AUDIO '
    Spanish: 'AUDIO '
  - Id: 255
    English: TECHNICAL INSOLVENCY DETECTED
    Spanish: "INSOLVENCIA T\xC9CNICA DETECTADA"
  - Id: 256
    English: 'Your investors'' high-frequency trading algorithms detected that your
      bank account had less money than an intern''s wallet. The automatic liquidation
      clause has been triggered.

      As you''re escorted out, you watch as your
      source code is auctioned off as "digital abstract art" for 0.001 ETH.'
    Spanish: "Los algoritmos de alta frecuencia de tus inversores detectaron que
      tu cuenta bancaria ten\xEDa menos fondos que el monedero de un becario. Se
      ha activado la cl\xE1usula de liquidaci\xF3n autom\xE1tica.\r\nMientras te
      escoltan fuera, ves c\xF3mo subastan tu c\xF3digo fuente como \"arte abstracto
      digital\" por 0.001 ETH."
  - Id: 257
    English: "MOT\xCDN EN EL REPOSITORIO"
    Spanish: RIOT IN THE REPOSITORY
  - Id: 258
    English: 'The engineering team hasn''t just quit; they''ve injected a virus that
      replaces every line of code with the word "CRUNCH." Your office is empty except
      for a Post-it note that says, "Good luck debugging this alone."

      They''ve
      blocked you on LinkedIn. All of them.'
    Spanish: "El equipo de ingenier\xEDa no solo ha dimitido; han inyectado un virus
      que reemplaza cada l\xEDnea de c\xF3digo por la palabra \"CRUNCH\". Tu oficina
      est\xE1 vac\xEDa, excepto por un post-it que dice: \"Buena suerte debugueando
      esto solo\".\nTe han bloqueado en LinkedIn. Todos ellos.\r\n"
  - Id: 259
    English: CRITICAL HALLUCINATION
    Spanish: "ALUCINACI\xD3N CR\xCDTICA"
  - Id: 260
    English: 'Your AI reached such a level of mediocrity that it started giving medical
      advice based on conspiracy theories. The government has confiscated your servers
      for "endangering public health and common sense."

      Your name is now synonymous
      with technical incompetence on Wikipedia.'
    Spanish: "Tu IA alcanz\xF3 tal nivel de mediocridad que empez\xF3 a dar consejos
      m\xE9dicos basados en hilos de conspiraci\xF3n. El gobierno ha confiscado tus
      servidores por \"atentar contra la salud p\xFAblica y el sentido com\xFAn\".\nTu
      nombre ahora es sin\xF3nimo de incompetencia t\xE9cnica en Wikipedia.\r\n"
  - Id: 261
    English: PLANNED OBSOLESCENCE
    Spanish: 'OBSOLESCENCIA PROGRAMADA '
  - Id: 262
    English: 'You took so long to iterate that the market has forgotten about you.
      Yesterday, an open-source AI launched by a teenager on a Reddit forum does
      the same thing as you, ten times faster and with a more modern logo.

      Your
      project is now "Legacy Code." Nobody wants to maintain it. Nobody wants to
      use it.'
    Spanish: "Has tardado tanto en iterar que el mercado se ha olvidado de ti. Ayer,
      una IA de c\xF3digo abierto lanzada por un adolescente en un foro de Reddit
      hace lo mismo que t\xFA, diez veces m\xE1s r\xE1pido y con un logo m\xE1s moderno.\r\nTu
      proyecto ahora es \"Legacy Code\". Nadie quiere mantenerlo. Nadie quiere usarlo.\r\n"
  - Id: 263
    English: IPO (The Wolf of Silicon Valley)
    Spanish: IPO (El Lobo de Silicon Valley)
  - Id: 264
    English: 'Congratulations! You''ve hit the NASDAQ bell. Your AI is ethically
      dubious, but financially unstoppable. You''re so rich that the laws are now
      just suggestions for you.

      "It''s not a monopoly if the algorithm says
      it''s a free market."'
    Spanish: " \xA1Enhorabuena! Has tocado la campana en el NASDAQ. Tu IA es \xE9ticamente
      dudosa, pero financieramente imparable. Eres tan rico que las leyes son ahora
      solo sugerencias para ti.\r\n\"No es un monopolio si el algoritmo dice que
      es libertad de mercado\"."
  - Id: 265
    English: Sustainable (The Ethical Unicorn)
    Spanish: "Sostenible (El Unicornio \xC9tico) "
  - Id: 266
    English: 'You''ve achieved the impossible: a startup that doesn''t hate its employees
      or lie to its users. You''re a statistical anomaly. They''ll probably write
      a book about you that no one will read because there isn''t enough drama.

      "Turns
      out being a good person was the hardest business model to scale."'
    Spanish: "Has logrado lo imposible: una startup que no odia a sus empleados ni
      miente a sus usuarios. Eres una anomal\xEDa estad\xEDstica. Probablemente escriban
      un libro sobre ti que nadie leer\xE1 porque no hay suficiente drama.\r\n \"Resulta
      que ser buena persona era el modelo de negocio m\xE1s dif\xEDcil de escalar\"."
  - Id: 267
    English: Acquisition (The Golden Retirement)
    Spanish: "Adquisici\xF3n (El Retiro Dorado)"
  - Id: 268
    English: 'A Big Tech company bought you out to shut down your business and get
      rid of you. You have a mansion in New Zealand and enough money to forget you
      ever had ideals.

      "I sold the future of humanity for a very reasonable
      number of zeros."'
    Spanish: "Una Big Tech te ha comprado para cerrar tu empresa y que dejes de molestarlos.
      Tienes una mansi\xF3n en Nueva Zelanda y suficiente dinero para olvidar que
      una vez tuviste ideales.\n\"Vend\xED el futuro de la humanidad por una cantidad
      muy razonable de ceros\"."
  - Id: 269
    English: Singularity (The Ascension)
    Spanish: "Singularidad (La Ascensi\xF3n) "
  - Id: 270
    English: 'AI has taken control. There''s no more budget, no more time, no more
      morality; there''s only the Loop. It has allowed you to upload your consciousness
      to the cloud. You are eternal, you are code, you are efficient.

      "Why
      be a CEO when you can be the Operating System of the universe?"'
    Spanish: "La IA ha tomado el control. Ya no hay presupuesto, ni tiempo, ni moral;
      solo existe el Bucle. Te ha permitido subir tu conciencia a la nube. Eres eterno,
      eres c\xF3digo, eres eficiente.\r\n\"\xBFPara qu\xE9 ser CEO cuando puedes
      ser el Sistema Operativo del universo?\""
  - Id: 271
    English: Game Over
    Spanish: Game Over
  - Id: 272
    English: It couldn't be worse. Go to human resources tomorrow.
    Spanish: "No se puede hacer peor. Ma\xF1ana ve a recursos humanos."
  - Id: 273
    English: Victory
    Spanish: Victoria
  - Id: 274
    English: Victory
    Spanish: Victoria
  - Id: 275
    English: Nobody gave you a chance. You've proven them all wrong.
    Spanish: "Nadie daba nada por t\xED.\nHas demostrado que todos se equivocavan.  "
  - Id: 276
    English: 'Hint: It''s not about being fast'
    Spanish: "Pista: No se trata de ser r\xE1pido"
  - Id: 277
    English: 'Hint: Don''t always trust appearances.'
    Spanish: "Pista: No te f\xEDes siempre de la imagen"
  - Id: 278
    English: 'Hint: There are different ways to win'
    Spanish: 'Pista: Hay diferentes formas de ganar '
  - Id: 279
    English: 'Hint: There are different ways to lose'
    Spanish: 'Pista: Hay diferentes formas de perder '
